watching and infant i might be getting a babysitting job watching my new baby cousin and i'm not nervous but can you please give me some tips on watching infants changing feeding and holding tips would be good i know how to do all that but any tips would help btw he is a boy thx thats awesome that you want to babysit babys are alot of fun however it all depends on the babys age hopefully the following can be helpful the st point of advice would be listen carefully to the mom she will give you the best tips on how to care for your cousin go with the flow of how the baby reacts when they cry usually remeber when you last fed if you just fed they are crying because they either need a diaper change need to picked up or are bored if you fed hours how often mom told you to feed they are probabley hungry tip on holding always hold neck most babys love to be propped up on shoulder to look over and see whats going on when cranky cradle in arms with being rocked or walked around swaying tips on diaper change always make sure the diaper is snug you would hate to have a leak the diaper tabs should be fairly close all depends on the width of the baby check the legs to to make sure the babies bum is in the middle of the diaper squirmy babies can make it difficutly for changes distract with a toy tips for feeding always make sure to burp make sure to ask mom the most questions on this topic if your nervous but above all always ask the mom questions if your unsure she knows her baby best it does not mean you are not capable of watching her child it usually shows that you are being responsible and wanting to do the best possible job hopefully some of my tips are helpful however best of luck Breastfeeding Teen Girl Squad Diaper Infant Aerial (dance move) Care Bears The Tracey Ullman Show shorts Charmed EastEnders Rugrats Urinary incontinence Infantilism Shaggy dog story Pitaten Kimi Finster Kodocha The Adventures of Pete & Pete Comanche Doug Calvin and Hobbes Toilet humour Garfield C